sentences.sentence: Morrison government had its own problemsThe subjective assessment of Aaron Patrick ("How Turnbull helped bring down Morrison", June 16) on the reasons for the downfall of the Morrison government is open to an alternative opinion.I am a swinging voter and have for whatever reason, like many others, moved with the tide of the state and country.The Morrison government was tossed out for administrative and economic incompetence, and an over- representation of the far right, clappy hands and other religious groups.

Australia is becoming more secular over time, and we need people to be representative of the increasing population of non-believers.The general attitude towards minority groups was appalling.The loss of grey matter with the departure of Julie Bishop and Malcolm Turnbull was substantial.The outlook is much brighter at the moment, the darkest spot is that we may not have an effective opposition for at least a decade.Owen CartledgeMalua Bay, NSWTimor-Leste visit was a missed opportunityWhile it is important for Foreign Minister Penny Wong to focus her immediate attention on the Solomon Islands ("Wong to seek Solomons assurance over China security pact", June 16) and other Pacific nations, an equally urgent priority should be Timor-Leste.Australia has good personal and diplomatic relations with the leaders of Timor-Leste, but thereby risks taking the relationship for granted - just as we did for so many years in the Pacific.Timor-Leste lies in a region that is strategically important to Australia, being close to vital oil and gas projects as well as global trade routes passing to the north.

Australia should be doing far more to help Timor-Leste develop its industries, infrastructure and skills to rise out of poverty.It was all very well for the Albanese government to visit Indonesia to strengthen relationships, but it was an opportunity lost not to have also visited Timor-Leste at the same time.Bob MuirheadPort Melbourne, VicWe need some answers on nuclear powerNyunggai Warren Mundine states the issue clearly ("The real energy joke is dismissing reliable nuclear out of hand", June 16).

When China is planning to build nuclear reactors and coal-fired power stations, one has to decide who knows the cost-benefit ratios: the Chinese government spending billions or the greens who only invest voice and placard power.John DysonShepparton, Vic
